714938f-a.text:
204 and 206 West 100th Street, south side, between Amsterdam Ave., and Broadway, as viewed westward, showing at the last number a 3-story structure housing the New York Free Circulating Library which today is part of the New York Public Library and is called the Bloomingdale Branch.  Bloomingdale Road formerly ran through this property at right angles to the street.  At the right is the 12-story Allenhurst, an apartment house at the S.E. corner of Broadway.

November 7, 1937.

F.L. Sperr.
